      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Surface Codex final answer candidates in activity",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Emit Codex app-server `phase: \"final_answer\"` answer-candidate activity records with `candidate`, `superseded`, and `selected` states.\n- Route those `stream: \"item\"` / `kind: \"answer_candidate\"` records into the Control UI Activity model and Activity view, so dashboard users can see the candidate lifecycle instead of losing it.\n- Keep answer-candidate activity out of IM/channel progress with `suppressChannelProgress: true`; final channel delivery still uses the selected final reply payload only.\n- Localize the new Control UI Activity labels through the existing i18n locale pipeline.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: Codex app-server can stream a `phase: \"final_answer\"` candidate, continue with tool work, then produce a later final answer. That native candidate history is real and useful for operator/debug surfaces, but messaging channels should still project one authoritative final answer. Before this update, answer-candidate `item` records were not connected to the Control UI Activity consumer; this PR now wires and renders them while keeping channel progress suppressed.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw repository on macOS, branch `agent/xiaozhua/codex-final-answer-candidates`, head `d0fe9a34f9f`, using the repository Vitest wrapper, the Control UI Activity renderer, the repository i18n checker, and a Vite-served Control UI proof page importing the real `renderActivity()` view from this branch.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts --testNamePattern=\"records superseded and selected final-answer candidates without changing the final reply\"\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts --testNamePattern=\"keeps suppressed answer candidates out of channel item progress\"\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/app-tool-stream.node.test.ts --testNamePattern=\"records answer candidates in activity from item events\"\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/activity.test.ts --testNamePattern=\"renders answer candidate activity with item facts and preview text\"\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/app-tool-stream.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/activity.test.ts\npnpm ui:i18n:check\npnpm exec oxlint ui/src/ui/activity-model.ts ui/src/ui/app-tool-stream.ts ui/src/ui/views/activity.ts ui/src/ui/app-tool-stream.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/activity.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts\ngit diff --check\n\n# Dashboard/activity visual proof: opened a temporary Vite-served Control UI page that imports\n# ./src/ui/views/activity.ts and renders two answer_candidate ActivityEntry records, expanded.\npnpm --dir ui dev --host 127.0.0.1 --port 5199\n# Browser snapshot / Playwright innerText from http://127.0.0.1:5199/activity-proof.html recorded below.\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Focused synthetic Codex stream test constructs `final_answer candidate (\"Draft answer\") → commandExecution tool → final_answer (\"Final answer\")` and verifies the terminal projection plus activity events:\n\n```text\nresult.assistantTexts == [\"Final answer\"]\nonPartialReply receives the streamed candidate text and later final text\nactivity item events include:\n  msg-early-final:    status=candidate   progressText=\"Draft answer\" suppressChannelProgress=true\n  msg-early-final:    status=superseded  progressText=\"Draft answer\" suppressChannelProgress=true\n  msg-selected-final: status=candidate   progressText=\"Final answer\" suppressChannelProgress=true\n  msg-selected-final: status=selected    progressText=\"Final answer\" suppressChannelProgress=true\n```\n\nThe channel-pipeline test verifies suppressed answer-candidate item events do not call channel `onItemEvent` / tool-progress callbacks while the run result payload remains:\n\n```text\n[{ text: \"Final answer\" }]\n```\n\nThe Control UI consumer/rendering tests verify the dashboard path that ClawSweeper flagged:\n\n```text\nui/src/ui/app-tool-stream.node.test.ts:\n  records answer candidates in activity from item events\n  activityEntries[0]: candidateStatus=superseded, summary=\"answer_candidate.superseded\", outputPreview=\"Draft answer\"\n  activityEntries[1]: candidateStatus=selected,   summary=\"answer_candidate.selected\",   outputPreview=\"Final answer\"\n\nui/src/ui/views/activity.test.ts:\n  renders answer_candidate with localized Activity text, Item: msg-early-final, and preview text \"Draft answer\"\n```\n\nRunning dashboard/activity surface output from the Vite-served Control UI proof page:\n\n```text\n2 of 2\nDONE\nanswer_candidate\nAnswer candidate superseded\n18:00:01\n1.2 s\nItem: msg-early-final\nRun: run-answer-candidates\nSession: main\nDraft answer\nDONE\nanswer_candidate\nAnswer candidate selected\n18:00:03\n1.4 s\nItem: msg-selected-final\nRun: run-answer-candidates\nSession: main\nFinal answer\n```\n\nFull related test/check output:\n\n```text\nextensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts: 79 passed\nsrc/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts: 183 passed\nui/src/ui/app-tool-stream.node.test.ts: 24 passed\nui/src/ui/views/activity.test.ts: 5 passed\npnpm ui:i18n:check: clean for 18 locales (fallback-only provider, fallbacks=35)\noxlint: Found 0 warnings and 0 errors\ngit diff --check: no output\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: Dashboard/activity subscribers now receive and render two Codex answer-candidate records for the `final_answer → tool → final_answer` stream, with the earlier candidate marked `superseded` and the final one marked `selected`. The activity records display candidate text in the Activity preview. IM/channel item progress still suppresses these records, and the selected final answer remains the only final reply payload. New Activity labels are routed through `t(...)` and synchronized across locale files.\n\nWhat was not tested: No live Telegram bot message was sent from this PR branch. The channel guarantee is covered at the auto-reply pipeline boundary that Telegram uses for item-progress callbacks and final reply payloads. The dashboard proof uses the real Control UI Activity view and a deterministic Vite-served fixture rather than a full live Gateway websocket run. Raw Codex native event persistence is unchanged by this patch.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts --testNamePattern=\"records superseded and selected final-answer candidates without changing the final reply\"`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts --testNamePattern=\"keeps suppressed answer candidates out of channel item progress\"`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/app-tool-stream.node.test.ts --testNamePattern=\"records answer candidates in activity from item events\"`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/activity.test.ts --testNamePattern=\"renders answer candidate activity with item facts and preview text\"`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/app-tool-stream.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/activity.test.ts`\n- `pnpm ui:i18n:check`\n- `pnpm exec oxlint ui/src/ui/activity-model.ts ui/src/ui/app-tool-stream.ts ui/src/ui/views/activity.ts ui/src/ui/app-tool-stream.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/activity.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n",
